						<summary>

						<p>On a slab near the <hi rend="italic">dhvajastaṁbha</hi> of the Chennakēśvarasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1563 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1487, Rudhirōdgārin, Āshāḍha śu. 15, Monday.</hi> If the Śaka year is a mistake for 1485, the details correspond to <hi rend="bold">1563 A.D., July 5,</hi> when there was a <hi rend="bold">lunar eclipse.</hi></p>						

						<p>The record stops with the mention of the king's name.</p>						

